[1] Cholera - Iraq: (Baghdad)
Date: Thu 29 Nov 2007
Source: Azzaman.com [edited]
<http://www.azzaman.com/english/index.asp?fname=news%5C2007-11-9%5Clad5.htm>


Sources at the Kadhimiya Teaching Hospital said 6 new cases of
cholera have been detected in Baghdad. The sources, refusing to be
named, said the government was trying hard not to let news about the
contagious disease spread in Baghdad where fears are rising of a
massive outbreak unless the disease is contained.

Medical personnel have discovered at least 80 more new cases of
cholera but the authorities would not let media report on the spread
of the disease. The sources say most of the new victims are children
from the most impoverished quarters east of the capital, which lack
basic amenities such as pure water. A source said cholera has caused
the death of 2 people in Baghdad.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[How many of these cases were included in the recent update is not at
all clear but, either way, the continued upswing in cases in Baghdad
is of concern.

A map of Iraq showing the location of Baghdad can be found at
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/iraq.pdf>. - Mod.LL]

