[5] Cholera - Nigeria: (Rivers)
Date: Sat 1 Dec 2007
Source: Nigerian Tribune [edited]
<http://www.tribune.com.ng/01122007/news/news11.html>


The people of Ajakajak community in Andoni Local Government Area of
Rivers State have cried out to the state government to rescue them
from a cholera outbreak, which has claimed the lives of more than 11
children as at press time on Thu 29 Nov 2007. A source in the
community told Saturday Tribune that the outbreak, which has
reportedly spread to some other communities in the area, was fast
assuming the form of an epidemic, threatening to wipe communities out.

Other sources from Ajakajak informed that records at the community's
health centre confirmed that the figure given was for last week alone
and that more cases had come in this week. It was gathered that the
epidemic was spreading very fast and that about 30 persons had died so far.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[A map of Nigeria showing the state of Rivers in the extreme southern
